events.name: Disease Outbreak with Hierarchy
events.ta1explanation: Root node for disease outbreak schema.

events.name: Compliance
events.ta1explanation: Compliance to a rule or regulation. Often negated, for example violating health regulations.

events.name: Generic Crime
events.ta1explanation: The disease outbreak could be the result of a crime, i.e., someone polluting the water with a chemical

events.name: Infections
events.ta1explanation: Invasion of an organism's body tissues by the virus. People can be infected by the virus in the disease outbreak

events.name: Illness
events.ta1explanation: Abnormal condition that negatively affects the structure or function of all or part of an organism due to the virus in the disease outbreak

events.name: Diagnosis
events.ta1explanation: Medical diagnosis on infection of the virus in the disease outbreak

events.name: Disinfect
events.ta1explanation: Disinfect contaminated areas
events.description: activity that purifies people, animals and objects of dirt and other particles

events.name: Treatment
events.ta1explanation: Attempted remediation of a health problem due to infection of the virus in the disease outbreak

events.name: Quarantine
events.ta1explanation: Restriction on the movement of people, animals and goods which is intended to prevent the spread of the disease

events.name: Gather Data
events.ta1explanation: Epidemiologic data collection

events.name: Collect Lab Samples
events.ta1explanation: Collecting and processing samples with the pathogen. These samples may not from the patient directly, but include food, water, surfaces, animals etc.

events.name: Analyze Data
events.ta1explanation: process of applying analytical methods to existing data of a specific type, breaking a complex topic or substance into smaller parts in order to gain a better understanding of it

events.name: Identify Outbreak
events.ta1explanation: Detecting a possible outbreak. Usually accompanied by an announcement.

events.name: Alert Authorities
events.ta1explanation: Alerting and reporting the detected outbreak to state and local public health authorities

events.name: Alert Population
events.ta1explanation: Alerting population of the exposure of the virus

events.name: Gov Health Decree
events.ta1explanation: Legislations were issued fighting the disease outbreak by government

events.name: Restrict Travel
events.ta1explanation: Restrictions on traveling to slow down the spread of the virus

events.name: Destruction
events.ta1explanation: The government destroys the source of the disease, for example, Haiti demolished the fishing nuts where the Cholera epidemic started.

events.name: Research
events.ta1explanation: Conducting research fighting the disease outbreak

events.name: Disease Prevention
events.description: acting to avoid the ocurrence of certain diseases in an organism or a population
events.ta1explanation: Develop disease-prevention measures or guidelines

events.name: Aid
events.ta1explanation: Financial assistance with food, housing and bills

events.name: New Treatments
events.ta1explanation: Developing effective treatment or cure for the disease

events.name: Inspection
events.description: organized examination or formal evaluation exercise, often involving the measurements, tests, and gauges applied to certain quality characteristics in comparison with specified requirements or standards
events.ta1explanation: Inspect the outbreak location and population to plan response.

events.name: Close Border
events.description: modification in the border or boundary of an administrative, electoral or political entity
events.ta1explanation: Close country borders to prevent disease spread

events.name: Distribute
events.ta1explanation: Distributing the vaccines of the virus
events.description: controlled distribution of scarce resources, goods, or services

events.name: ExchangeBuySell
events.ta1explanation: Buying, selling or exchanging goods related to the disease outbreak

events.name: Donate
events.ta1explanation: Charitable activities related to the disease outbreak

events.name: Assignment
events.description: moment or event when something is formally granted
events.ta1explanation: Officials are assigned to monitor, prevent, contain, and mitigate the disease outbreak

events.name: Information Campaign
events.ta1explanation: Use of media to raise public awareness of the disease.

events.name: Debunk Misinformation
events.ta1explanation: Debunking misinformation of related to the disease outbreak

events.name: Create Artifact
events.ta1explanation: Creation of a disease by laboratories or organizations

events.name: Climate Change
events.ta1explanation: Contemporary climate change may contribute to the disease outbreak, i.e., global warming

events.name: Lack of Sanitation
events.description: public health conditions related to clean drinking water and adequate disposal of human excreta and sewage
events.ta1explanation: Negated, showing lack of a clean environment.

events.name: Poor Hygiene
events.description: set of practices performed for the preservation of health
events.ta1explanation: Negated, showing lack of practices preserving health.

events.name: Inadequate Food Safety
events.description: scientific discipline describing handling, preparation, and storage of food in ways that prevent foodborne illness
events.ta1explanation: Negated, showing lack of measures that prevent foodborne illness.

events.name: Unclean Drinking Water
events.ta1explanation: Negated, showing state of unclean water.

events.name: IdentifyDiseaseSource
events.ta1explanation: Investigation of the disease outbreak includes identify the source of the virus as well as the suspect of the creator

events.name: Contact
events.ta1explanation: Make contact with the suspect

events.name: Arrest
events.ta1explanation: Taking the suspect who created the virus or violated laws during the outbreak into custody

events.name: Inspect
events.ta1explanation: Organized examination or formal evaluation on the suspect for creating the virus

events.name: Contact Attorney
events.description: act of conveying intended meanings from one entity or group to another through the use of mutually understood signs and rules
events.ta1explanation: Plaintiff contacts attorney to begin filing a lawsuit

events.name: File Complaint
events.ta1explanation: Plaintiff files a complaint to initiate a lawsuit

events.name: Answer
events.ta1explanation: In law, a solemn assertion in opposition to someone or something by the defendant

events.name: Discovery
events.ta1explanation: Pre-trial procedure in common law countries for obtaining evidence

events.name: Motion
events.ta1explanation: In US law, a procedural device to bring a limited, contested issue before a court for decision

events.name: Mediation
events.ta1explanation: Dispute resolution with assistance of an impartial third party moderator throughthe use of communication and negotiation techniques

events.name: Settlement
events.ta1explanation: The dispute is resolved through a payment of money.

events.name: Education
events.ta1explanation: learning in which knowledge and skills are transferred through teaching. The defendant is educated about regulations.

events.name: Trial
events.ta1explanation: Coming together of parties to a dispute, to present information in a tribunal

events.name: Judgement
events.ta1explanation: The formal decision made by a court following a lawsuit

events.name: Appeal
events.ta1explanation: Resort to a superior court to review the decision of an inferior court or administrative agency

events.name: Testing
events.ta1explanation: A viral test checks specimens from your nose or your mouth to find out if you are currently infected with the virus

events.name: Tracing
events.ta1explanation: Contact tracing identifies persons who may have come into contact with an infected person during the disease outbreak

events.name: Identify Exposed People
events.description: mapping of an entity known or recognizable by certain features to anabstract conventional entity by which it will be known and designatedwithout ambiguity
events.ta1explanation: Identify people exposed to the virus or came into contact with the infected person.

events.name: Quarantine Exposed Group
events.description: epidemiological intervention of restriction on the movement of peopleand goods, which is intended to prevent the spread of infectious diseaseor pests
events.ta1explanation: Quarantine and monitor people who came into contact with the infected person.

events.name: Biological Warfare
events.ta1explanation: The disease outbreak may result from the use of biological toxins or infectious agents such as bacteria, viruses, insects, and fungi with the intent to kill, harm or incapacitate humans, animals or plants as an act of war

events.name: Mutate life
events.ta1explanation: The virus may undergo an alteration in the nucleotide sequence of the genome during the disease outbreak

events.name: Recover
events.ta1explanation: Patients may recover from the infection of the virus

events.name: Die
events.ta1explanation: Patients may die from the infection of the virus

events.name: Funeral
events.ta1explanation: A ceremony for patients died in the disease outbreak

events.name: Mutation
events.ta1explanation: The virus may undergo an alteration in the nucleotide sequence of the genome during the disease outbreak

events.name: Construction
events.ta1explanation: Field hospitals may be constructed to accommodate patients during the outbreak

events.name: Collaborate
events.ta1explanation: Research collaboration on finding treatment for the virus

events.name: Meeting
events.ta1explanation: Academic conference or scientific conference for conducting research on fighting the virus

events.name: Sanitize
events.ta1explanation: Disinfection to prevent infection of the virus

events.name: Wash
events.ta1explanation: Washing hands to prevent infection

events.name: Comply
events.ta1explanation: Complying to the government legislations

events.name: Wear
events.ta1explanation: Wearing masks to prevent the spread of virus

events.name: Educate
events.ta1explanation: Sharing and educating related knowledge for fighting the disease outbreak

events.name: Social Distancing
events.ta1explanation: Keep physical distance to prevent the spread of the disease

events.name: Vaccinate
events.ta1explanation: Vaccine intended to provide acquired immunity against the virus

events.name: Exchange
events.ta1explanation: Buying, selling or exchanging goods related to the disease outbreak

events.name: Demonstrate
events.ta1explanation: Protests over responses to the disease outbreak

events.name: Business Close
events.ta1explanation: Business close due to the disease outbreak

events.name: Business Reopen
events.ta1explanation: Business reopen due to the disease outbreak

events.name: Handcuffing
events.ta1explanation: Using handcuffs to secure a suspect who violated law during the disease outbreak

events.name: Interrogation
events.ta1explanation: Interviewing with the goal of eliciting useful information related to suspected crime during the disease outbreak

events.name: Restrain
events.ta1explanation: Physical restraint on the suspect

events.name: Discussion
events.ta1explanation: conversation between two or more people on responding to the disease outbreak

events.name: Inject
events.ta1explanation: The act of administering a liquid, especially a drug, into a patient infected by the virus using a needle and a syringe

events.name: Consume
events.ta1explanation: Consumption of a substance by an organism

events.name: Eat
events.ta1explanation: Ingestion of food to provide for all organisms their nutritional or medicinal needs

events.name: Drink
events.ta1explanation: Ingesting water or other liquids into the body through the mouth

events.name: Contact Through Skin
events.ta1explanation: Route through which substances may be received

events.name: Contaminate Substance
events.comment: Pathogen contaminates object, which is later consumed.
events.ta1explanation: Presence of an unwanted constituent, harmful substance or impurity in a material, physical body, or environment

events.name: Purchase Contaminated Object
events.comment: optional event for purchasing contaminated food or drink.
events.ta1explanation: transfer of equivalent goods to each other.

events.name: Transmission
events.ta1explanation: passing of a pathogen causing communicable disease from an infected host individual or group to other individual or group, regardless of whether the other individual was previously infected

events.name: Business Shutdown
events.ta1explanation: Business close permanently due to the disease outbreak

entities.name: consumer, person in contact with the infectant
